---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Methodology - ApprovalPrep" description="A clear explanation of how ApprovalPrep helps users prepare truthful self-service paperwork." canonical="https://approvalprep.com/methodology">
  <section class="hero shell methodology-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Methodology</p>
    <h1>How ApprovalPrep works.</h1>
    <p class="lead">ApprovalPrep helps people turn a messy paperwork moment into a clearer self-service packet. The method is simple: use true facts, gather real support, write plainly, review carefully, and send materials yourself.</p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="button primary-button" href="/letter-writing-studio">Start free for $0</a>
      <a class="button secondary-button" href="/pricing">Compare kits</a>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="band">
    <div class="shell methodology-steps">
      <article class="card"><span>1</span><h2>Choose the situation</h2><p>Start with the job: explain a gap, prepare for rental review, organize income proof, respond to a credit question, or assemble a loan-ready packet.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><span>2</span><h2>Gather real support</h2><p>Use documents you already have or can honestly obtain. ApprovalPrep does not help create fake records, false statements, or misleading proof.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><span>3</span><h2>Write plainly</h2><p>Use short, factual language. The goal is not to sound like a lawyer. The goal is to make the reviewer’s job easier without overpromising.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><span>4</span><h2>Review and send yourself</h2><p>Check dates, names, facts, attachments, and tone. You stay responsible for what you send and where you send it.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="band">
    <div class="shell two">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">What it is</p>
        <h2>Self-service preparation.</h2>
        <p>ApprovalPrep provides templates, checklists, examples, guided prompts, and downloadable files to help users organize their own materials before an application, explanation, or document request.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="notice warning">
        <strong>What it is not:</strong>
        <p>No legal advice. No financial advice. No credit repair service. No third-party contact. No fake documents. No approval guarantee.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
